antReference><gtr:abstractText>&lt;p>Dr. Rowe's postdoctoral project will expand upon the anthropological fieldwork with Lebanese Maronite Catholic diasporic communities conducted for her PhD. Her doctoral thesis, Lebanese Lives in New England: American Narratives of Assimilation and Ethno-Racial Classification, examined ethnic identity, religiosity, inter-generational cultural transmission, intermarriage, and management of &amp;quot;heritage&amp;quot; among second- and third-generation Lebanese.&lt;/p>

&lt;p>While the resounding emphasis amongst her informants was their &amp;quot;assimilated&amp;quot; American status (ie disavowing a shared identity or affiliation with other Lebanese people around the world), when referencing their faith, a strategic Lebanese Maronite identity and social obligations based on kinship were readily claimed. Questions about how and why faith-based ties and corresponding identity claims are being crafted long after cultural assimilation is said to have occurred will guide Dr. Rowe's research. She will reframe her fieldwork findings by incorporating more interdisciplinary literature; enhance her area specialisation though collaboration with Middle East specialists; and foster scholarly exchange with others who work on the Lebanese Diaspora, eg through the Institute for Migration Research (Lebanese American University) and the Lebanese Emigration Research Centre (Notre Dame University). Dr. Rowe will prepare journal articles and seminar presentations, continue with Arabic language study, and receive training to expand her teaching qualifications. &lt;br />&lt;/p></gtr:abstractText><gtr:fund><gtr:end>2010-03-31</gtr:end><gtr:funder url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/organisation/924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE"><gtr:id>924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE</gtr:id><gtr:name>ESRC</gtr:name></gtr:funder><gtr:start>2009-04-01</gtr:start><gtr:type>INCOME_ACTUAL</gtr:type><gtr:valuePounds>60028</gtr:valuePounds></gtr:fund><gtr:output><gtr:artisticAndCreativeProductOutputs/><gtr:collaborationOutputs/><gtr:disseminationOutputs/><gtr:exploitationOutputs/><gtr:furtherFundingOutputs/><gtr:impactSummaryOutputs/><gtr:intellectualPropertyOutputs/><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications/><gtr:identifiers><gtr:identifier type="RCUK">ES/G008868/1</gtr:identifier>